b'"As COVID-19 started to develop, TaxAid and Tax Help for Older people were really at the front of my mind. There were a lot of issues that they were facing. A lot of their usual avenues for fundraising weren't open to them, and they were faced with the difficulty of working from home. We provided laptops to them to allow them to work from home. We helped them set up a home contact center, and our internal communications team helped out with a social media campaign. It's been really great to hear feedback from our volunteers about the difference they've made and how much it inspired them to have been able to impact people's lives in that way." Rachel Austin, Deloitte UK Tax Director. 

As long-standing partners of  TaxAid and Tax Help for Older People, the Deloitte UK Tax and Legal practice reached out to see how they could help. They provided a wide range of services drawing on expertise from across the firm. [link in story]

b'\xe2\x80\x9cIn India, a lot of migrant laborers come to large cities to find work. Due to this COVID situation and the lockdown, a lot of these are out of work," says Ankit. "So we thought that how do we support in a manner that we can soften the impact? And the immediate thought which came to our mind was, why don't we support them with food? One meal may not matter as much to me, but it means a whole lot to the person receiving it.\xe2\x80\x9d

One small act of kindness inspired a movement. After seeing the impact of one meal given to a migrant worker, Ankit Goel of @deloitteindia :India: and a group of friends had the idea to organize an effort to combat food insecurity. On just the first day alone, Ankit and his friends were able to feed three hundred people, and have since served over 250,000 meals. [link in story]

b'This year marks the 50th Anniversary of many #Pride :rainbow_flag_selector: celebrations around the world. Pride commemorates the Stonewall Uprising which began with a black trans woman, Marsha P Johnson, standing up for her rights.

At Deloitte, we know how important it is that all of our people can live and work freely and peacefully as their true, authentic selves, and are united against any form of social injustice. We are committed to #LGBT+ inclusion and believe in the power of #allyship, whereby all our people support the rights and wellbeing of their LGBT+ colleagues \xe2\x80\x93 visibly and vocally supporting the LGBT+ community inside and outside of Deloitte.

As part of our global virtual Pride celebration, we asked some of our LGBT+ colleagues what Pride means to them, and why they think allyship is important. Tell us in the comments below what Pride means to you, and why you believe allyship matters.'

b"So many women find it daunting to return to work after starting a family. But it doesn\xe2\x80\x99t have to be. Deloitte\xe2\x80\x99s #ReturnToWork programs prove that a little support goes a long way.
.
It was 2018 and Catherine was joining Deloitte Australia's Consulting practice, enriched by thirteen years of life and three children.
.
\xe2\x80\x9cWhen I started, I realized something: it doesn\xe2\x80\x99t matter how long you\xe2\x80\x99ve been out - you still have the same skills and capability. The only thing you lose is confidence, and you can regain it quickly\xe2\x80\x9d [link in story]
